": "88e14def3b2911d6e574aca21de4988128ed3fe8d3bd506c5a67adc36a399bb3", "text": "parameters ...................................................................................................... 26 Appendix D: Additional notes .............................................................................................................................. 27 v List of figures Figure 1: Restoration opportunity areas: Top ten state/regions .............................................................................. 10 List of tables Table 1: Weighted MCA criteria. .................................................................................................................................8 Table 2: National figures rounded to nearest one-thousand ......................................................................................9 Table 3: Data sources.............................................................................................................................................. 16 Table 4: Additional data considered. ....................................................................................................................... 28 List of maps Map 1: Priority restoration areas. ............................................................................................................................ 13 Map 2: Forest canopy cover loss (D1) and Map 3: Dry deciduous forest loss (D2). ............................................... 18 Map 4: Mangrove forest loss (D3) and Map 5: Combined forest loss (D4). ............................................................ 18 Map 6: Basin and forest loss (P1) and Map 7: Priority watersheds above waterbodies (P2). ................................ 19 Map 8: River corridors (P3) and Map 9: Key Biodiversity Areas (P4). .................................................................... 19 Map 10: High slope areas (P5) and Map 11: Watersheds with towns (P6).......................................................